feUtilTest.scala, which is good, but I'm not sure about the dynamic-access class in Memory.java since it isn't a test class.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Recalling Scala nested class names**\\n\\nI’m thinking about how Scala compiles its objects and nested classes. A Scala object named \\\"A\\\" would compile to \\\"A$.class.\\\" If there's a nested class \\\"B\\\" inside that object, it might be represented as \\\"A$B.class.\\\" Since it's a static class, I can access it with the syntax \\\"A.B.\\\" That feels correct, so I’m glad I could clarify that for myself!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Identifying potential issues**\\n\\nI’m considering how the Gradle Scala plugin source set includes both Java and Scala. There's a potential problem with having the Java test helper as a top-level public class, which needs to be a “test class.” Thankfully, it is public, so that's good. However, I’m still wondering about the note to “use upstream test sources only as behavioral examples.” That seems important for clarity in a testing context, so I’ll keep that in mind moving forward.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented focused coverage for `akka.protobufv3.internal.UnsafeUtil`.\n\nChanged files:\n- `tests/src/com.typesafe.akka/akka-protobuf-v3_3/2.6.21/src/test/scala/com_typesafe_akka/akka_protobuf_v3_3/UnsafeUtilTest.scala`\n  - Initializes `UnsafeUtil` in an Android-like environment to reach the `determineAndroidSupportByAddressSize` `Class#getMethod` call sites.\n  - Invokes `allocateInstance` via `MethodHandle` and verifies constructor bypass behavior.\n\n- `tests/src/com.typesafe.akka/akka-protobuf-v3_3/2.6.21/src/test/java/libcore/io/Memory.java`\n  - Adds a minimal `libcore.io.Memory` shim so `Android.isOnAndroidDevice()` becomes true and the Android support checks execute.\n\n- `tests/src/com.typesafe.akka/akka-protobuf-v3_3/2.6.21/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/reachability-metadata.json`\n  - Registers the test shim methods for Native Image reflection lookup.\n  - Registers the constructor-guarded test type for unsafe allocation.\n\nI did not compile or run tests, per instructions.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_045ef19f335f2caf0169f7a0403090819f95ffad5128fc9f76\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 349, "output": 1810, "cacheRead": 62464, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 64623, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1777836072774, "responseId": "resp_045ef19f335f2caf0169f7a0295274819f9545e232678cc8ca"}, "toolResults": []}
